File: A medical worker tests for the coronavirus. JOHANNESBURG - The Health Department reported 53 more people have succumbed to COVID-19. According to the department, 15 of the new deaths occurred in the past 24 to 48 hours. The COVID-19 death toll in South Africa is at 19,164. Over 2,000 new cases have been recorded. READ: Gauteng acting-Health MEC promises to prioritise stability The cumulative number of detected COVID-19 cases in SA is 721,770. Recoveries in SA are at 649,935. The recovery rate is at 90%. Health Media Statement 29 October 2020.Pages Final by eNCA.com on Scribd  - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.